results.wikipedia_summary: Pygmy Owls are members of the genus Glaucidium. They belong to the typical owl family Strigidae, one of the two generally accepted living families of owls The genus consists of about 26 to 35 species distributed worldwide. The exact number of species is somewhat disputed.
